From: Aria2-Pro-Core <noreply@example.com>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Platform: make OpenSSL 'legacy' provider load non-fatal

OpenSSL 3.x ships the legacy provider as a separate dynamically loaded
module (legacy.so). Fully-static aria2c builds do not bundle that
module, so OSSL_PROVIDER_load(NULL, "legacy") fails at startup and
aria2c aborts before it can run.

aria2 only needs the legacy provider for RC4 (some BitTorrent message
stream encryption peers). Treat its absence as a soft failure: continue
without it. The default provider remains required.

---
 src/Platform.cc | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/Platform.cc b/src/Platform.cc
--- a/src/Platform.cc
+++ b/src/Platform.cc
@@ -122,5 +122,9 @@
   // RC4 is in the legacy provider.
   legacy_provider_ = OSSL_PROVIDER_load(nullptr, "legacy");
   if (!legacy_provider_) {
-    throw DL_ABORT_EX("OSSL_PROVIDER_load 'legacy' failed.");
+    // OpenSSL ships the legacy provider as a separate dynamic module
+    // (legacy.so). Fully-static aria2c builds do not bundle it, so
+    // the load fails at startup. The legacy provider is only required
+    // for RC4 (a few BitTorrent peers); continue without it instead
+    // of aborting the whole binary.
   }
